│ the legacy model to proceed with vectorization.\n\nThe       │
│ assertion failure immediately after the SE analysis confirms │
│ that the `loop-vectorize` pass begins its planning,          │
│ encounters the cost model disagreement, and aborts.\n\n###   │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis\n\nThe root cause is an architectural │
│ limitation in the legacy cost model's profitability          │
│ analysis. It relies heavily on a statically determinable     │
│ trip count to decide if vectorization is profitable. When    │
