│ gracefully by evaluating costs under the assumption of       │
│ vectorization and doesn't get blocked by the low minimum     │
│ trip count in the same way.\n\nThe fix is to align the VPlan │
│ cost model's behavior with the legacy model's limitations in │
│ this specific scenario. If the legacy model determines that  │
│ vectorization is impossible due to a small trip count, the   │
│ VPlan model should respect that decision and also select a   │
