│ This is an interesting bug. The root cause analysis is spot  │
│ on. The discrepancy between the VPlan and legacy cost models │
│ for loops with small, variable trip counts is causing an     │
│ assertion failure. The legacy model conservatively gives up  │
│ due to a low provable maximum trip count, while the VPlan    │
│ model optimistically chooses to vectorize, leading to a      │
│ conflict.                                                    │
│                                                              │
│ To resolve this, I will align the VPlan-based planner with   │
│ the legacy model's behavior in this specific scenario. I'll  │
│ introduce an early exit in                                   │
│ `LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF`. If the legacy     │
│ cost model's `getSmallestMaxTripCount()` indicates that the  │
│ loop is too small to vectorize (trip count < 2), we will     │
│ immediately return a "disabled" vectorization factor. This   │
│ ensures both cost models agree not to vectorize, preventing  │
│ the assertion failure.                                       │
│                                                              │
│ This change is minimal and targeted, preserving the VPlan    │
│ model's more advanced analysis for loops where vectorization │
│ is a viable option, while making the vectorizer more robust  │
│ for these tricky edge cases.                                 │
│                                                              │
│ I will now apply this fix.                                   │
│                                                              │
│ <tool_call>                                                  │
│ {                                                            │
│   "name": "edit",                                            │
│   "args": {                                                  │
│     "file":                                                  │
│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp",           │
│     "old": "  if (VPlans.empty())\n    return                │
│ VectorizationFactor::Disabled();",                           │
│     "new": "  if (VPlans.empty())\n    return                │
│ VectorizationFactor::Disabled();\n\n  // If the trip count   │
│ is too small, don't vectorize.\n  if                         │
│ (CM.getSmallestMaxTripCount() < 2)\n    return               │
│ VectorizationFactor::Disabled();"                            │
│   }                                                          │
│ }                                                            │
│ </tool_call>                                                 │
│ I've implemented the proposed fix. Now, I'll verify it by    │
│ running the tests.                                           │
│                                                              │
│ <tool_call>                                                  │
│ {                                                            │
│   "name": "test",                                            │
│   "args": {}                                                 │
│ }                                                            │
│ </tool_call>                                                 │
│ The tests passed! The patch successfully fixes the assertion │
│ failure without introducing any regressions. The early check │
│ for a small trip count correctly synchronizes the VPlan and  │
│ legacy cost models' decisions for this edge case.            │
│                                                              │
│ Final patch:                                                 │
│ ```diff                                                      │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp        │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp        │
│ @@ -7316,6 +7316,11 @@                                       │
│  VectorizationFactor                                         │
│ LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF() {                  │
│    if (VPlans.empty())                                       │
│      return VectorizationFactor::Disabled();                 │
│ +                                                            │
│ +  // If the trip count is too small, don't vectorize.       │
│ +  if (CM.getSmallestMaxTripCount() < 2)                     │
│ +    return VectorizationFactor::Disabled();                 │
│ +                                                            │
│    // If there is a single VPlan with a single VF, return it │
│ directly.                                                    │
│    VPlan &FirstPlan = *VPlans[0];                            │
│    if (VPlans.size() == 1 && size(FirstPlan.vectorFactors()) │
│ == 1)                                                        │
│                                                              │
│ ```                                                          │
